The larger net moisture transport into the Arctic in the NP-
Warm case results in enhanced Arctic surface warming through a
number of processes and feedbacks: greater latent heat transfer
from the subpolar extratropics to Arctic, greater increase in the
area of low clouds in the Arctic and attendant absorption of
infrared radiation, and greater amounts of atmospheric water
vapor in the Arctic and attendant clear-sky absorption of infrared
radiation. The relative magnitude of these effects discussed above
